<subSubSection pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="88.[151,1436,613,1755]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
Diagnosis: Fourth costal section 0.6 times as long as third costal section. Cross-vein R-M between 1/3 and 1/2 of discal cell. Hairs on tegula: 6–7 stronger brown setae. T5 3.5–4 times as long as ST8. SES clear, with hairs on border with SS; gonopods symmetrical; hypandrium with broadened lobes; phallic guide narrowing at tip, but rounded, with hairs at base; phallus with very short branches distally and with membranous lobes along the whole 
<collectingCountry box="[151,190,758,781]" name="Philippines" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">PH</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
